Vice President Kamala Harris visited the Ritz Theatre and Museum in Jacksonville, Florida to address the issue of banning books and distorting history in education. She expressed her concern about the national agenda to ban books and promote false narratives. Harris emphasized the importance of teaching the truth and providing children with accurate information. She criticized politicians who push propaganda and mislead students, calling for teachers to be able to teach facts without fear of losing their jobs. Harris drew parallels to past attempts to distort history, such as Holocaust denial and erasing the mistreatment of Native Americans and Japanese internment camps. She urged the audience to unite and fight against these divisive agendas, emphasizing the strength that comes from remembering and learning from our history. Harris concluded by encouraging everyone to stand up for what is right and fight for justice and equality.